title: Bay Bridge designer fears leaks are damaging main cable
text:
Photo: Justin Sullivan, Getty Images A worker walks on the Bay Bridge eastern span’s main cable, which the bridge’s lead designer says is vulnerable to corrosion because of leaking rainwater. A worker walks on the Bay Bridge eastern span’s main cable, which...
The cable that holds up the new Bay Bridge eastern span is vulnerable to corrosion because of rainwater leaking into its anchorages, the bridge’s lead designer has warned Caltrans — a threat that the agency has previously downplayed on the $6.4 billion project.
